but they were involved in some kind
of blackmailing scheme.

245
00:23:09.901 --> 00:23:13.112
Although. Trev always
complained about his cut a lot.

246
00:23:13.947 --> 00:23:16.865
That's how he got the idea
for us to start pulling our own scams.

247
00:23:16.866 --> 00:23:19.993
like the one on you. behind Dennis's back.

248
00:23:19.994 --> 00:23:23.665
But… I guess Dennis found out.

249
00:23:26.292 --> 00:23:27.460
Why me?

250
00:23:28.336 --> 00:23:31.089
He knew he could apply pressure on you
because of your kid.

251
00:23:32.298 --> 00:23:34.758
I mean.
he-he also said something else.

252
00:23:34.759 --> 00:23:37.428
Something about what went down
in Portland?

253
00:23:42.183 --> 00:23:44.269
I-I-I don't know what he's talking about.

254
00:23:45.103 --> 00:23:47.563
Well. he liked you.

255
00:23:47.564 --> 00:23:49.107
He was just an ambitious guy.

256
00:23:49.649 --> 00:23:50.775
Plus you were local.

257
00:23:53.027 --> 00:23:55.154
And he said that you had
exploitable weaknesses.

258
00:23:56.114 --> 00:23:58.700
But those sound like words
he probably learned from Dennis.

259
00:24:00.118 --> 00:24:01.828
Dennis. Yeah.

260
00:24:02.745 --> 00:24:07.749
The guy you were gonna hand me over to.
Tied to a fucking chair.

261
00:24:07.750 --> 00:24:09.168
We were desperate.

262
00:24:09.752 --> 00:24:12.296
I screwed everything up. okay?
I got Sky killed...

263
00:24:12.297 --> 00:24:14.591
You're not gonna get any
fucking sympathy from me.

264
00:24:15.592 --> 00:24:20.762
I didn't do anything wrong.
and I got arrested for Sky's murder.

265
00:24:20.763 --> 00:24:23.098
And for Trevor's. Yeah.

266
00:24:23.099 --> 00:24:25.309
- What? That-That makes no sense.
- I know.

267
00:24:25.310 --> 00:24:26.810
Dennis killed them both.

268
00:24:26.811 --> 00:24:30.857
I-I-I assume he killed Trevor.
but I heard him kill Sky.

269
00:24:31.441 --> 00:24:32.442
You heard him?

270
00:24:33.026 --> 00:24:35.694
You… Well. then you're a… a witness.

271
00:24:35.695 --> 00:24:37.613
- I mean. I guess.
- Yeah.

272
00:24:37.614 --> 00:24:39.656
I-I didn't see anything. I...

273
00:24:39.657 --> 00:24:43.243
No. but you could… you could exonerate me.
You know it-it was him.

274
00:24:43.244 --> 00:24:45.245
You… Y-You have to talk to the cops.

275
00:24:45.246 --> 00:24:47.039
- You have to tell them.
- No! No. I'm not talking...

276
00:24:47.040 --> 00:24:48.290
- Yes!
- I'm not getting involved.

277
00:24:48.291 --> 00:24:49.541
What… Why… What… What?

278
00:24:49.542 --> 00:24:50.876
- No cops.
- You're already involved.

279
00:24:50.877 --> 00:24:52.461
- What are you talking about?
- No cops. No!

280
00:24:52.462 --> 00:24:56.507
Do you think Sky would want me
to go to jail for something I didn't do?

281
00:24:57.425 --> 00:24:59.886
Like. have my entire life exploded?

282
00:25:00.470 --> 00:25:01.471
Fuck.

283
00:25:02.347 --> 00:25:04.014
<i>This is the one. Bax.</i>

284
00:25:04.015 --> 00:25:07.935
Luck is coming back my way.
as long as Aaron Judge doesn't screw me.

285
00:25:07.936 --> 00:25:09.019
Mm-hmm.

286
00:25:09.020 --> 00:25:13.983
Oh! Check it out.
My boy finally got a name.

287
00:25:14.567 --> 00:25:17.320
Say hello to Chester.
After my grandfather.

288
00:25:18.071 --> 00:25:21.241
I don't wanna be rude. but that's the name
of a cat who dies a virgin.

289
00:25:22.116 --> 00:25:24.159
No. Grandpa Chet was nice like that.

290
00:25:24.160 --> 00:25:27.621
Grandpa Chet shook your hand.
you had twins.

291
00:25:27.622 --> 00:25:29.123
Ugh.

292
00:25:30.917 --> 00:25:32.042
Gonzales.

293
00:25:32.043 --> 00:25:34.211
Hey. it's Paula. Paula Sanders.

294
00:25:34.212 --> 00:25:38.549
Paula Sanders. I heard you made bail.
How was Rikers?

295
00:25:38.550 --> 00:25:41.468
They still have that
sweet chicken teriyaki on Thursdays?

296
00:25:41.469 --> 00:25:45.013
Uh. are-are you gonna be
at the station in about an hour?

297
00:25:45.014 --> 00:25:47.558
I'm coming in with someone
who can exonerate me.

298
00:25:47.559 --> 00:25:49.184
- <i>Paula. we already</i>...
- Someone who knows

299
00:25:49.185 --> 00:25:53.398
that it was Dennis O'Neill.
Trevor's boyfriend. who's the real killer.

300
00:25:54.524 --> 00:25:55.525
I'll be here.

301
00:25:59.821 --> 00:26:01.239
She's coming in.

302
00:26:04.784 --> 00:26:07.786
"I went on a journey with my coworkers
to hell and back

303
00:26:07.787 --> 00:26:11.123
with only a dead man's
hacked burner phone to guide us."

304
00:26:11.124 --> 00:26:13.375
- What the fuck are you doing?
- What the fuck are you doing?

305
00:26:13.376 --> 00:26:14.877
You broke into my desk?

306
00:26:14.878 --> 00:26:16.336
You lied to my face.

307
00:26:16.337 --> 00:26:20.258
Okay. I knew you were. like.
a hustler or whatever. but…

308
00:26:20.758 --> 00:26:22.092
How could you do this?

309
00:26:22.093 --> 00:26:25.596
Please. you're the one who said that
you and Paula weren't even real friends.

310
00:26:25.597 --> 00:26:28.056
Sure. but I didn't straight
betray her. okay.

311
00:26:28.057 --> 00:26:31.894
You would withhold information
and let her go to jail to write a story?

312
00:26:31.895 --> 00:26:35.480
To… To get a better job or something?
Are you fucking kidding me. Geri?

313
00:26:35.481 --> 00:26:37.983
Okay. first of all. yes.
I got into the phone.

314
00:26:37.984 --> 00:26:39.569
But there was nothing on it.

315
00:26:41.446 --> 00:26:44.156
And it is not my fault
that Paula went to jail.

316
00:26:44.157 --> 00:26:46.451
The police thinks she's a murderer.
and so do you.

317
00:26:47.118 --> 00:26:48.994
Okay. I know we say horrible things
to each other.

318
00:26:48.995 --> 00:26:52.873
but I thought we were. like. real friends.

319
00:26:52.874 --> 00:26:53.957
We are.

320
00:26:53.958 --> 00:26:56.919
Okay? If you wanted something this badly.
you would have done the same thing.

321
00:26:56.920 --> 00:27:00.505
It's not my fault that you don't know what
it is you wanna do with your life yet.

322
00:27:00.506 --> 00:27:04.051
Last year it was day trading. and now
it's. "Oh. maybe I'll go to law school."

323
00:27:04.052 --> 00:27:06.929
Okay. well.
I'd rather not know what I want.

324
00:27:06.930 --> 00:27:10.265
than want something so bad
I'm willing to shaft my friends to get it.

325
00:27:10.266 --> 00:27:13.895
You're overreacting. as usual.
Just like you did with Vi.

326
00:27:18.107 --> 00:27:19.817
You know what? Fuck this!

327
00:27:20.485 --> 00:27:21.486
Rudy.

328
00:27:22.278 --> 00:27:23.446
Come on.

329
00:27:24.364 --> 00:27:25.990
No witty retort?

330
00:27:32.997 --> 00:27:34.541
Witty retort.

331
00:27:43.132 --> 00:27:45.300
Thank you so much. All right. hi.

332
00:27:45.301 --> 00:27:47.928
I'm Paula Sanders.
I'm here to see Detective Gonzales.

333
00:27:47.929 --> 00:27:49.638
- She's expecting me.
- She's expecting you?

334
00:27:49.639 --> 00:27:51.014
All right. Hang on.

335
00:27:51.015 --> 00:27:53.016
Uh. do…
…you have a bathroom I could use?

336
00:27:53.017 --> 00:27:54.476
- Yeah. Down that way.
- Okay.

337
00:27:54.477 --> 00:27:56.520
- Hurry.
- Um. Gonzales?

338
00:27:56.521 --> 00:27:57.689
- Somebody's here for you.
- Hey.

339
00:27:59.065 --> 00:28:01.525
- She'll be right down. Yeah.
- Yeah? Okay. great.

340
00:28:01.526 --> 00:28:03.443
Do I have to sign?

341
00:28:03.444 --> 00:28:04.571
No. nothing.

342
00:28:10.577 --> 00:28:11.578
Fuck!

343
00:28:14.747 --> 00:28:17.791
- Hey! What the hell. man? Dude!
- Oh! Oh. oh fuck.

344
00:28:17.792 --> 00:28:19.085
Ah. sorry.

345
00:28:19.961 --> 00:28:22.546
Oh. sorry.
I should've trusted you.

346
00:28:22.547 --> 00:28:25.925
- Yeah!
- Yeah. it's just. um. not cool.

347
00:28:28.219 --> 00:28:29.220
Ash. sorry.

348
00:28:32.348 --> 00:28:33.349
Ash?

349
00:28:36.186 --> 00:28:37.603
Oh! Hey!

350
00:28:43.067 --> 00:28:44.277
F… Fuck.

351
00:29:09.302 --> 00:29:10.719
What's up?

352
00:29:15.183 --> 00:29:16.184
Paula.

353
00:29:17.435 --> 00:29:19.771
Where's the magical witness
who's supposed to clear your name?

354
00:29:21.022 --> 00:29:23.232
She ran away.

355
00:29:23.233 --> 00:29:25.860
I guess I'll see you in court then.

356
00:29:26.653 --> 00:29:27.862
Hey. what good are you?

357
00:29:28.696 --> 00:29:30.823
What earthly good are you?

358
00:29:31.741 --> 00:29:34.576
You know. Dennis O'Neill killed
those people. not me.

359
00:29:34.577 --> 00:29:36.578
I'm a fucking regular person!

360
00:29:36.579 --> 00:29:40.749
Now I'm caught up in this mess of lies
and disappearing bodies

361
00:29:40.750 --> 00:29:44.127
and two jailhouse lawyers
with the same fucking name.

362
00:29:44.128 --> 00:29:46.547
- Two lawyers?
- You were supposed to...

363
00:29:46.548 --> 00:29:50.051
You didn't help me in the beginning.
and you're not helping me now.

364
00:29:50.718 --> 00:29:53.847
You're the only person who's supposed to.
and you're fucking useless!

365
00:30:10.154 --> 00:30:11.155
Top you up?

366
00:30:11.739 --> 00:30:12.740
Sure. yeah.

367
00:31:28.066 --> 00:31:29.067
Okay.

368
00:31:46.042 --> 00:31:47.418
<i>- Hi!
- Hey!</i>

369
00:31:48.002 --> 00:31:49.212
<i>Sorry I'm late.</i>

370
00:31:50.296 --> 00:31:52.839
<i>How's my favorite food scientist?</i>

371
00:31:52.840 --> 00:31:56.134
<i>Good. good. Busy. busy.</i>

372
00:31:56.135 --> 00:31:59.388
<i>All right.
Shall we start experimenting?</i>

373
00:32:03.726 --> 00:32:08.106
<i>I'm gonna make you feel so good.
You deserve it.</i>

374
00:32:18.992 --> 00:32:20.577
<i>You just need to relax.</i>

375
00:32:23.705 --> 00:32:25.247
<i>Fucking commute
is just killing me.</i>

376
00:32:25.248 --> 00:32:26.583
<i>Fucking odd…</i>

377
00:32:27.750 --> 00:32:29.002
<i>Show me your body.</i>

378
00:32:34.173 --> 00:32:36.426
<i>You look amazing.</i>
